/* Ramzey Ghanaim
 * Web Browser Proxy
 *
 * This program is a local proxy that blocks
 * HTTP websites listed in the bin/forbidden.txt
 * file.
 * 
 * NOTE: HTPS does not work.
 *****************
 * FILES:
 *
 *
 * Makefile - File used for automating the build process
 *          
 *
 *
 * src/proxy.c - Main proxy program that intercepts web traffic, filters it,
 *               and sends data to a server, and sends messages back to a browser.
 *
 * README - This file
 * 
 *
 * doc/Documentation.pdf - Describes the design of the project, 
 *                         including specification of protocol.
 *
 * bin/forbidden.txt - server info file.
 *
 *
 *
 *
 *  FEATURES:
 *
 *      1. Once compiled, type "make run" to run the program with a default
 *         port of 8080 and a forbidden file of "forbidden.txt".
 *
 *      2. Support for missing packets is not supported.
 *
 *      3. logged requests are place in the file "access.log" that is generated
 *         in the directory the proxy is ran.
 *     
 *      4. http (not https) Tested sites include, but not limited to:
 *         
 *                  example.com
 *                  pudim.com.br
 *                  stealmylogin.com
 *                  zdnet.com
 * 
 *
*/